0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Pruning means the machine keeps recent working state and enough local data for) Tj
0 -12 Td
(normal small-node use. It does not keep full archived history.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(For this public experiment, assume the node is optimized around recent data and) Tj
0 -12 Td
(that historical data older than roughly 20 days may need another source.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Why this matters:) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Recent transaction sending and live monitoring can work from the local node.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Older blocks, receipts, logs, or traces may not be available locally.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(- Full archived history requires much more storage and a different design.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(If you need historical data beyond local retention, use one of these approaches.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Option 1: Query another data provider) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
