0 -12 Td
(an indexer, an explorer, a data platform, or another provider of your choosing,) Tj
0 -12 Td
(as long as that source supports the Monad data you need.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Simple workflow:) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(1. Decide what you need: blocks, receipts, logs, fills, balances, or tax/export) Tj
0 -12 Td
(   records.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(2. Export or query the data from the provider.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(3. Save the raw export separately from your trading logic.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(4. Normalize the fields into your own database or CSV files.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(5. Cross-check important records against your local node when the data is still) Tj
0 -12 Td
(   inside local retention.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(This is the easiest path for most non-infrastructure users.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
